Third-party software

The locked npm package map contains 832 non-root package entries; the installed subset varies by operating system and CPU. License metadata summary at release review: MIT 678; Apache-2.0 60; ISC 41; MPL-2.0 13; LGPL-3.0-or-later 10; BSD-2-Clause 8; BSD-3-Clause 6; Apache-2.0 AND LGPL-3.0-or-later 3; 0BSD 2; and one each under CC0-1.0, CC-BY-4.0, Python-2.0, Unlicense, BlueOak-1.0.0, MIT/ISC, MIT/WTFPL, BSD/MIT/Apache, MPL/Apache, Apache/LGPL, and Apache/LGPL/MIT combinations. One transitive package (`seq-queue`) omits its SPDX field but includes an MIT license file.

Direct runtime dependencies and their package metadata licenses:

- MIT: @hookform/resolvers, @monaco-editor/react, @next/env, Radix UI packages, better-sqlite3, clsx, monaco-editor, Next.js, React, react-dom, react-hook-form, react-markdown, Recharts, remark-gfm, tailwind-merge, Zod.
- Apache-2.0: Prisma client/SQLite adapter, class-variance-authority, OpenAI JavaScript client.
- ISC: lucide-react.

The optional `@img/sharp-libvips-linux-x64` transitive package reports LGPL-3.0-or-later. `caniuse-lite` reports CC-BY-4.0 for browser compatibility data. Retain npm's installed license files when redistributing dependency binaries.

Piston

The Docker Compose file references the Engineer Man Piston image by digest. Piston is an independent MIT-licensed service and is not bundled into this source tree. Downloaded language runtimes, container layers, and their licenses remain separate third-party components. Review their notices before redistributing images or runtime packages.

